data.meta_description: English Monarch. Queen consort of King Edward I Longshanks. The daughter of Ferdinand III of Castile (St. Ferdinand) and Joan of Ponthieu, she was married to Edward in 1250. She was 13, Edward was 15. Although this was purely an arranged, political marriage, it developed into a strong love affair. The couple had 16...
